  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a significant portion of which has already been restitution. While embezzlement is a breach of trust, sentencing guidelines for first-time offenders in this category typically emphasize probation, community service, or short periods of incarceration to act as a deterrent. The outburst from the spectator is irrelevant to the legal sentencing process and has been disregarded. A sentence of 6 months serves as a punitive measure that reflects the seriousness of the theft while allowing for potential rehabilitation, given the lack of criminal history.",
  "verdict": 6
}
